<p>I faced the same problem on Pop_!OS, no need to reboot actually;
The easier way is to just restart GNOME by one of two ways:</p>

<ul>
  <li>pressing <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Alt</code> + <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">F2</code>, type <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">r</code> then <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Enter</code>, or</li>
  <li>in terminal:</li>
</ul>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ killall -3 gnome-shell
</code></pre></div></div>

